<div id="review_235664877" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/235664877" />
    <a title="Bobby" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4196-bobby"><img alt="Bobby" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1194936191p2/4196.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/235664877?book_show_action=true">Nov 14, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bobby" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bobby" href="/user/show/4196-bobby">Bobby</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4196-bobby?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer235664877" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11345556088118899629">Krugman already has one Nobel (for economics); he should get another for writing about economic policy in a way that&apos;s actually easy to understand and enjoyable! In this surprisingly fast read he explains--among other things--the fundamental goals of &quot;movement conservatism,&quot; the historical context of FDR&apos;s era and the New Deal, and the worsening social inequality that has been going on for the last few decades. It&apos;s refreshing to hear intelligent arguments backed up with data, though Krugman doe</span>
  <span id="freeText11345556088118899629" style="display:none">Krugman already has one Nobel (for economics); he should get another for writing about economic policy in a way that's actually easy to understand and enjoyable! In this surprisingly fast read he explains--among other things--the fundamental goals of "movement conservatism," the historical context of FDR's era and the New Deal, and the worsening social inequality that has been going on for the last few decades. It's refreshing to hear intelligent arguments backed up with data, though Krugman doesn't go over the top with with statistics etc (rightly so IMHO since this is meant for the lay public). Though Krugman's left-of-center beliefs clearly come across, I think people from all political backgrounds should be able to appreciate his evidence-based conclusions and recommendations. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11345556088118899629" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


